# Harbormaster secrets — copy to .env and fill in.
# .env is gitignored; .env.example is committed.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tailscale sidecar
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Generate at https://login.tailscale.com/admin/settings/keys.
# Recommended settings:
#   - Reusable: yes (allows recovery without generating a new key)
#   - Ephemeral: no (we want a stable machine identity)
#   - Expiration: 90 days (the default is fine; key is dormant after first boot)
#
# This key is used ONLY on first boot or during disaster recovery (when the
# tailscale-state volume is lost). Once the sidecar is registered on the
# tailnet, go to https://login.tailscale.com/admin/machines → find the `api`
# machine → "Disable key expiry". From then on, the node identity persists
# until the volume is lost; the TS_AUTHKEY env var can expire harmlessly.
TS_AUTHKEY=tskey-auth-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# Optional: extra args passed to `tailscaled up`. Usually empty.
TS_EXTRA_ARGS=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LiteLLM master key — root credential for API calls
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# THE root key. Used to mint virtual keys via the admin API and to bypass
# per-key restrictions. Must start with `sk-`. Rotate if leaked.
# Generate: echo "sk-harbormaster-$(openssl rand -hex 24)"
LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=sk-harbormaster-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LiteLLM salt key — IMMUTABLE
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Encrypts model API keys stored in Postgres (virtual keys, per-deployment
# credentials). Rotating this AFTER the first model is added makes existing
# stored credentials undecryptable. Treat as a one-and-done secret.
# Generate once: echo "sk-salt-$(openssl rand -hex 24)"
LITELLM_SALT_KEY=sk-salt-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Admin UI login
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Username/password for the UI at https://api.tail8bd569.ts.net/ui.
# Separate from the master key (which is for API calls). The simplest
# homelab auth — SSO is supported but overkill for our scale.
UI_USERNAME=admin
UI_PASSWORD=XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Postgres — backs the UI, virtual keys, spend tracking, request logs
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Internal to the compose stack (not exposed on the tailnet). Generate
# a random password — 32+ chars, never rotated unless leaked.
# Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
